    <Descriptive_Notes>
      <Descriptive_Note>
        <Note_Text>Smooth, lemon yellow colored wood of the species Calycohyllum candidissimum, native to Cuba, Mexico, Columbia, and Venezuela. It is used for structures, millwork, carving, fishing rods, archery bows, and tool handles.</Note_Text>
        <Note_Language>English</Note_Language>
